  "title": "Marine Superintendent",
  "description": "<p><strong>JOB DESCRIPTION</strong></p><ul><li>Maintain vessel, including spare parts arrangements, repairing monitoring and visual inspection when they drop in Singapore </li><li>To manage all service reports and weekly monthly report from our fleet. </li><li>Able to travel overseas at short notices depend of our fleet and docking plan. </li><li>Mantain good working relations with our onboard crew by daily communications by email and phone basis under their supervisor and other team member to prevent any issues. </li><li>Physically fit to work under outdoor conditions</li><li>Able to work overtime and under pressure</li></ul><p><strong>JOB REQUIREMENTS</strong></p><ul><li>Graduate in Marine Engineering field </li><li>working experience in ship operation management and maintenance of the vessel. </li><li>Onboard experience in ship operations</li><li>Familar with the industry standards and compliance requirements</li><li>Mature and strong responsibility</li><li>Ability to travel within short notice as required</li><li>Possess positibe work attitude with efficiency </li><li>good inter-personal skills </li><li>Able to work in a team environment independently with minimum supervision </li></ul><p><br /></p>",
